<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <%- include('../partials/head') %>
  <script type="application/ld+json">
  {
    "@context": "https://schema.org",
    "@type": "FAQPage",
    "mainEntity": [
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "What is the difference between BaZi and Chinese Zodiac?",
        "acceptedAnswer": {
          "@type": "Answer",
          "text": "BaZi (Four Pillars of Destiny) is a comprehensive birth chart system that uses your exact birth date and time to calculate four pillars based on Heavenly Stems and Earthly Branches, producing a detailed destiny map. The Chinese Zodiac is a simpler system that assigns one of 12 animal signs based only on your birth year. BaZi includes the zodiac animal as one component but goes far deeper with element analysis, Yin/Yang polarity, and pillar interactions."
        }
      },
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "Is Chinese astrology more accurate than Western astrology?",
        "acceptedAnswer": {
          "@type": "Answer",
          "text": "Chinese and Western astrology use fundamentally different frameworks and serve different purposes. Chinese astrology, especially BaZi, focuses on destiny mapping, life cycles, and elemental balance using the lunar calendar and Five Elements. Western astrology focuses on personality traits and psychological tendencies using the solar calendar and planetary positions. Many practitioners find the two systems complementary rather than competing."
        }
      },
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "What are the Five Elements in Chinese astrology?",
        "acceptedAnswer": {
          "@type": "Answer",
          "text": "The Five Elements (Wu Xing) are Wood, Fire, Earth, Metal, and Water. They form the energetic foundation of all Chinese metaphysical systems. Each element governs specific traits, organs, seasons, and directions. They interact through a Production Cycle (Wood fuels Fire, Fire creates Earth, Earth yields Metal, Metal collects Water, Water nourishes Wood) and a Control Cycle (Wood controls Earth, Earth controls Water, Water controls Fire, Fire controls Metal, Metal controls Wood)."
        }
      },
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "How do I find my Chinese zodiac animal?",
        "acceptedAnswer": {
          "@type": "Answer",
          "text": "Your Chinese zodiac animal is determined by your birth year following the lunar calendar. The 12 animals cycle in this order: Rat, Ox, Tiger, Rabbit, Dragon, Snake, Horse, Goat, Monkey, Rooster, Dog, and Pig. For example, 2024 is the Year of the Dragon. Note that the Chinese New Year falls between late January and mid-February, so if you were born in January or early February, your zodiac animal may be from the previous year. Use a BaZi calculator for the most accurate result."
        }
      }
    ]
  }
  </script>
</head>
<body class="seo-page">
  <div style="padding:16px 24px;">
    <a href="/app"><img src="/Logos/SVG/rev-vert.svg" alt="WoBazi" height="32"></a>
  </div>

  <main class="seo-main" style="max-width:800px;margin:0 auto;padding:0 16px 64px;">

    <!-- ═══ Hero ═══ -->
    <div class="about-hero">
      <div class="about-hanzi">命理</div>
      <h1 style="color:var(--text);font-size:26px;margin-bottom:10px;">Chinese Astrology</h1>
      <p>Explore the ancient Chinese metaphysical systems that have guided billions of lives for over three millennia — from BaZi and the Chinese Zodiac to Five Element theory and Yin-Yang philosophy.</p>
    </div>

    <!-- ═══ Section 1: Overview ═══ -->
    <div class="about-section">
      <h2 style="font-size:18px;color:var(--text);margin-bottom:12px;">🌏 What Is Chinese Astrology?</h2>
      <p>Chinese astrology is one of the world's oldest and most comprehensive divination systems, spanning more than 3,000 years of continuous practice. Unlike casual horoscopes, Chinese astrology encompasses a family of interconnected disciplines — each offering a unique lens into destiny, personality, timing, and spatial harmony.</p>
      <div class="about-callout">
        <strong>Key difference from Western astrology:</strong> Chinese astrology is built on the lunar calendar, the Five Elements (Wood, Fire, Earth, Metal, Water), and the dynamic interplay of Yin &amp; Yang — rather than solar months and planetary positions.
      </div>
      <p>At its core, Chinese astrology views the universe as an interconnected web of cyclical energies. Your birth moment captures a unique snapshot of these energies — your personal cosmic blueprint — which skilled practitioners can decode to reveal your strengths, challenges, relationships, and life trajectory.</p>
    </div>

    <!-- ═══ Section 2: Five Major Systems ═══ -->
    <div class="about-section">
      <h2 style="font-size:18px;color:var(--text);margin-bottom:16px;">📚 Five Major Chinese Astrology Systems</h2>
      <p>Chinese metaphysics contains several distinct yet interconnected systems. Each serves a different purpose, from personal destiny reading to strategic planning and environmental design.</p>
    </div>

    <div style="display:grid;grid-template-columns:repeat(auto-fit,minmax(200px,1fr));gap:14px;margin-bottom:20px;">
      <div class="about-section" style="text-align:center;padding:24px 16px;">
        <div style="font-size:36px;margin-bottom:8px;">🏛️</div>
        <h3 style="font-size:15px;margin-bottom:4px;">BaZi</h3>
        <div style="font-size:12px;color:var(--gold,#f0c040);margin-bottom:8px;">八字 &mdash; Four Pillars of Destiny</div>
        <p style="font-size:12px;">The most detailed personal destiny system. Uses your exact birth date and time to construct four pillars of Heavenly Stems and Earthly Branches, revealing your elemental makeup, personality, career path, and life cycles.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="about-section" style="text-align:center;padding:24px 16px;">
        <div style="font-size:36px;margin-bottom:8px;">🐉</div>
        <h3 style="font-size:15px;margin-bottom:4px;">Chinese Zodiac</h3>
        <div style="font-size:12px;color:var(--gold,#f0c040);margin-bottom:8px;">生肖 &mdash; 12 Animal Signs</div>
        <p style="font-size:12px;">The most widely known system. Assigns one of 12 animal archetypes based on your birth year, each carrying distinct personality traits, compatibility patterns, and fortune tendencies in a 12-year repeating cycle.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="about-section" style="text-align:center;padding:24px 16px;">
        <div style="font-size:36px;margin-bottom:8px;">⭐</div>
        <h3 style="font-size:15px;margin-bottom:4px;">Zi Wei Dou Shu</h3>
        <div style="font-size:12px;color:var(--gold,#f0c040);margin-bottom:8px;">紫微斗数 &mdash; Purple Star Astrology</div>
        <p style="font-size:12px;">An intricate star-charting system that maps over 100 stars across 12 life palaces. Offers extremely detailed readings on career, wealth, relationships, health, and spiritual growth through celestial positioning.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="about-section" style="text-align:center;padding:24px 16px;">
        <div style="font-size:36px;margin-bottom:8px;">🧭</div>
        <h3 style="font-size:15px;margin-bottom:4px;">Qi Men Dun Jia</h3>
        <div style="font-size:12px;color:var(--gold,#f0c040);margin-bottom:8px;">奇门遁甲 &mdash; Strategic Divination</div>
        <p style="font-size:12px;">Originally a military strategy tool, this system excels at timing and decision-making. Used to select auspicious dates for business launches, negotiations, travel, and other critical life events.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="about-section" style="text-align:center;padding:24px 16px;">
        <div style="font-size:36px;margin-bottom:8px;">🏠</div>
        <h3 style="font-size:15px;margin-bottom:4px;">Feng Shui</h3>
        <div style="font-size:12px;color:var(--gold,#f0c040);margin-bottom:8px;">风水 &mdash; Environmental Energy</div>
        <p style="font-size:12px;">The art of aligning your living and working spaces with natural energy flows. Feng Shui uses compass directions, element theory, and landform analysis to optimize health, wealth, and harmony in your environment.</p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- ═══ Section 3: Five Elements ═══ -->
    <div class="about-section">
      <h2 style="font-size:18px;color:var(--text);margin-bottom:12px;">🔥 The Five Elements (五行 Wu Xing)</h2>
      <p>The Five Elements form the energetic backbone of all Chinese astrology. Every person, moment, and space can be described through the balance and interaction of these five forces. Understanding your elemental composition is the key to reading any Chinese astrological chart.</p>
    </div>

    <div style="display:grid;grid-template-columns:repeat(5,1fr);gap:10px;margin-bottom:16px;">
      <% const elTraits = { Wood: ['Growth','Creativity','Flexibility'], Fire: ['Passion','Joy','Dynamism'], Earth: ['Stability','Nurturing','Grounding'], Metal: ['Precision','Discipline','Clarity'], Water: ['Wisdom','Adaptability','Depth'] }; %>
      <% Object.keys(bazi.EL_ZH).forEach(el => {
        const emojis = { Wood:'🌳', Fire:'🔥', Earth:'🏔️', Metal:'⚔️', Water:'🌊' };
      %>
        <div class="about-section" style="text-align:center;padding:20px 10px;border-top:3px solid <%= bazi.EL_COLOR[el] %>;">
          <div style="font-size:28px;margin-bottom:6px;"><%= emojis[el] %></div>
          <div style="font-size:22px;font-family:'Noto Sans SC',sans-serif;color:<%= bazi.EL_COLOR[el] %>;font-weight:700;"><%= bazi.EL_ZH[el] %></div>
          <h3 style="font-size:14px;margin:6px 0 8px;color:<%= bazi.EL_COLOR[el] %>;"><%= el %></h3>
          <% elTraits[el].forEach(trait => { %>
            <span style="display:inline-block;font-size:10px;padding:2px 8px;margin:2px;border-radius:20px;background:<%= bazi.EL_COLOR[el] %>22;color:<%= bazi.EL_COLOR[el] %>;"><%= trait %></span>
          <% }); %>
        </div>
      <% }); %>
    </div>

    <div class="about-section">
      <h3 style="font-size:15px;margin-bottom:12px;">🔄 Production Cycle (相生)</h3>
      <p style="font-size:13px;margin-bottom:14px;">Each element nourishes and gives rise to the next in a continuous cycle of creation:</p>
      <div style="display:flex;align-items:center;justify-content:center;flex-wrap:wrap;gap:4px;font-size:14px;">
        <% bazi.PRODUCTION_CYCLE.forEach((el, i) => { %>
          <span style="padding:5px 12px;border-radius:20px;background:<%= bazi.EL_COLOR[el] %>22;color:<%= bazi.EL_COLOR[el] %>;font-weight:600;font-size:13px;"><%= el %></span>
          <span style="color:var(--muted);">→</span>
        <% }); %>
        <span style="padding:5px 12px;border-radius:20px;background:<%= bazi.EL_COLOR['Wood'] %>22;color:<%= bazi.EL_COLOR['Wood'] %>;font-weight:600;font-size:13px;">Wood</span>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="about-section">
      <h3 style="font-size:15px;margin-bottom:12px;">⚡ Control Cycle (相克)</h3>
      <p style="font-size:13px;margin-bottom:14px;">Each element also restrains and controls another, maintaining cosmic balance:</p>
      <div style="display:flex;flex-direction:column;gap:8px;align-items:center;">
        <% Object.entries(bazi.CONTROL_CYCLE).forEach(([from, to]) => { %>
          <div style="display:flex;align-items:center;gap:8px;font-size:13px;">
            <span style="padding:4px 12px;border-radius:20px;background:<%= bazi.EL_COLOR[from] %>22;color:<%= bazi.EL_COLOR[from] %>;font-weight:600;min-width:60px;text-align:center;"><%= from %></span>
            <span style="color:var(--gold,#f0c040);">conquers</span>
            <span style="padding:4px 12px;border-radius:20px;background:<%= bazi.EL_COLOR[to] %>22;color:<%= bazi.EL_COLOR[to] %>;font-weight:600;min-width:60px;text-align:center;"><%= to %></span>
          </div>
        <% }); %>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- ═══ Section 4: The 12 Chinese Zodiac Animals ═══ -->
    <div class="about-section">
      <h2 style="font-size:18px;color:var(--text);margin-bottom:12px;">🐲 The 12 Chinese Zodiac Animals (十二生肖)</h2>
      <p>The Chinese Zodiac is a 12-year cycle in which each year is represented by an animal sign. Your birth year determines your zodiac animal, which influences your personality, compatibility, and fortune. The cycle has been used for centuries to mark time, guide relationships, and forecast luck.</p>
    </div>

    <div style="display:grid;grid-template-columns:repeat(3,1fr);gap:14px;margin-bottom:20px;">
      <%
        const animalOrder = ['Rat','Ox','Tiger','Rabbit','Dragon','Snake','Horse','Goat','Monkey','Rooster','Dog','Pig'];
        const baseYears = { Rat:1924, Ox:1925, Tiger:1926, Rabbit:1927, Dragon:1928, Snake:1929, Horse:1930, Goat:1931, Monkey:1932, Rooster:1933, Dog:1934, Pig:1935 };
      %>
      <% animalOrder.forEach((animal, idx) => {
        const branch = bazi.BRANCHES[idx];
        const z = bazi.ZODIAC[animal];
        const years = [];
        for (let y = baseYears[animal]; y <= 2032; y += 12) years.push(y);
      %>
        <div class="about-section" style="text-align:center;padding:20px 12px;">
          <div style="font-size:32px;margin-bottom:4px;"><%= branch.emoji %></div>
          <h3 style="font-size:15px;margin-bottom:2px;"><%= animal %></h3>
          <div style="font-size:18px;font-family:'Noto Sans SC',sans-serif;color:var(--gold,#f0c040);margin-bottom:8px;"><%= bazi.ANIMAL_ZH[animal] %></div>
          <div style="display:flex;flex-wrap:wrap;justify-content:center;gap:4px;margin-bottom:10px;">
            <% z.traits.forEach(trait => { %>
              <span style="font-size:10px;padding:2px 8px;border-radius:20px;background:rgba(240,192,64,0.1);color:var(--gold,#f0c040);"><%= trait %></span>
            <% }); %>
          </div>
          <div style="font-size:10px;color:var(--muted,#888a9e);line-height:1.5;">
            <%= years.join(', ') %>
          </div>
        </div>
      <% }); %>
    </div>

    <style>
      @media (max-width: 600px) {
        .seo-main [style*="grid-template-columns:repeat(3,1fr)"] {
          grid-template-columns: repeat(2, 1fr) !important;
        }
        .seo-main [style*="grid-template-columns:repeat(5,1fr)"] {
          grid-template-columns: repeat(3, 1fr) !important;
        }
      }
      @media (max-width: 380px) {
        .seo-main [style*="grid-template-columns:repeat(5,1fr)"] {
          grid-template-columns: repeat(2, 1fr) !important;
        }
      }
    </style>

    <!-- ═══ Section 5: Chinese vs Western Astrology ═══ -->
    <div class="about-section">
      <h2 style="font-size:18px;color:var(--text);margin-bottom:16px;">⚖️ Chinese vs Western Astrology</h2>
      <p>While both traditions seek to understand human nature through celestial patterns, they differ fundamentally in method, philosophy, and focus.</p>

      <div style="margin-top:16px;display:flex;flex-direction:column;gap:0;">
        <%
          const comparisons = [
            { aspect:'Calendar',   chinese:'Lunar (Yin) calendar',            western:'Solar (Tropical) calendar' },
            { aspect:'Cycle',      chinese:'60-year sexagenary cycle',        western:'12-month zodiac cycle' },
            { aspect:'Elements',   chinese:'5 — Wood, Fire, Earth, Metal, Water', western:'4 — Fire, Earth, Air, Water' },
            { aspect:'Focus',      chinese:'Destiny mapping & life timing',   western:'Personality & psychological traits' },
            { aspect:'Polarity',   chinese:'Yin & Yang',                      western:'Masculine & Feminine' },
            { aspect:'Based On',   chinese:'Birth date + exact time',         western:'Birth month (sun sign position)' },
          ];
        %>
        <% comparisons.forEach((row, i) => { %>
          <div style="display:grid;grid-template-columns:100px 1fr 1fr;gap:12px;padding:12px 14px;font-size:12px;border-radius:<%= i === 0 ? '10px 10px' : (i === comparisons.length - 1 ? '0 0 10px 10px' : '0') %>;background:<%= i % 2 === 0 ? 'rgba(240,192,64,0.04)' : 'rgba(255,255,255,0.02)' %>;border:1px solid rgba(240,192,64,<%= i % 2 === 0 ? '0.08' : '0.03' %>);border-top:<%= i > 0 ? 'none' : '' %>;">
            <div style="font-weight:700;color:var(--gold,#f0c040);"><%= row.aspect %></div>
            <div style="color:var(--text,#f0f0ff);"><%= row.chinese %></div>
            <div style="color:var(--muted,#888a9e);"><%= row.western %></div>
          </div>
        <% }); %>
      </div>

      <div style="display:grid;grid-template-columns:1fr 1fr;gap:10px;margin-top:12px;font-size:11px;text-align:center;">
        <div style="padding:6px 10px;border-radius:8px;background:rgba(240,192,64,0.06);color:var(--gold,#f0c040);font-weight:600;">☯ Chinese</div>
        <div style="padding:6px 10px;border-radius:8px;background:rgba(255,255,255,0.04);color:var(--muted,#888a9e);font-weight:600;">♈ Western</div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- ═══ Section 6: Yin & Yang ═══ -->
    <div class="about-section">
      <h2 style="font-size:18px;color:var(--text);margin-bottom:12px;">☯ Yin & Yang (阴阳)</h2>
      <p>Yin and Yang is the foundational duality underlying all Chinese metaphysical thought. Rather than opposing forces, they represent complementary aspects of a single whole — endlessly transforming into each other, maintaining cosmic equilibrium.</p>
    </div>

    <div style="display:grid;grid-template-columns:1fr 1fr;gap:14px;margin-bottom:16px;">
      <div class="about-section" style="text-align:center;padding:24px 16px;border-top:3px solid #f0c040;">
        <div style="font-size:32px;margin-bottom:8px;">☀️</div>
        <h3 style="font-size:16px;color:#f0c040;margin-bottom:8px;">Yang 阳</h3>
        <div style="display:flex;flex-direction:column;gap:6px;font-size:12px;color:var(--text,#f0f0ff);">
          <span>Light &amp; Brightness</span>
          <span>Active &amp; Expansive</span>
          <span>Masculine Energy</span>
          <span>Heat &amp; Summer</span>
          <span>Odd Numbers</span>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="about-section" style="text-align:center;padding:24px 16px;border-top:3px solid #6366f1;">
        <div style="font-size:32px;margin-bottom:8px;">🌙</div>
        <h3 style="font-size:16px;color:#6366f1;margin-bottom:8px;">Yin 阴</h3>
        <div style="display:flex;flex-direction:column;gap:6px;font-size:12px;color:var(--text,#f0f0ff);">
          <span>Dark &amp; Mystery</span>
          <span>Receptive &amp; Contractive</span>
          <span>Feminine Energy</span>
          <span>Cold &amp; Winter</span>
          <span>Even Numbers</span>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="about-callout">
      <strong>In BaZi, every Heavenly Stem carries both an element AND a Yin/Yang polarity</strong> — creating 10 distinct Stem types (5 elements x 2 polarities). This means two people born in "Wood" years can have very different charts depending on whether their Wood is Yang (甲 Jia — towering tree energy) or Yin (乙 Yi — flexible vine energy). This nuance is what makes BaZi far more precise than the Chinese Zodiac alone.
    </div>

    <!-- ═══ FAQ Section ═══ -->
    <div class="about-section">
      <h2 style="font-size:18px;color:var(--text);margin-bottom:16px;">❓ Frequently Asked Questions</h2>

      <div class="about-faq">
        <div class="about-faq-item">
          <div class="about-faq-q">What is the difference between BaZi and Chinese Zodiac?</div>
          <div class="about-faq-a">
            <p>The Chinese Zodiac assigns one of 12 animal signs based solely on your birth year, giving a broad personality overview. BaZi (Four Pillars of Destiny) is far more detailed — it uses your exact birth date and time to calculate four pillars, each composed of a Heavenly Stem and Earthly Branch. This produces a nuanced chart revealing your Day Master element, elemental balance, personality depth, career potential, relationship dynamics, and 10-year life cycles. Think of the Zodiac as your headline; BaZi is the full biography.</p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="about-faq-item">
          <div class="about-faq-q">Is Chinese astrology more accurate than Western astrology?</div>
          <div class="about-faq-a">
            <p>Rather than being "more" or "less" accurate, these two traditions answer different questions using different frameworks. Chinese astrology (especially BaZi) maps destiny, timing, and elemental balance through the lunar calendar and Five Elements. Western astrology analyzes personality and psychological patterns using the solar calendar and planetary positions. Many experienced practitioners study both systems as complementary tools, finding that together they provide a more complete picture than either alone.</p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="about-faq-item">
          <div class="about-faq-q">What are the Five Elements in Chinese astrology?</div>
          <div class="about-faq-a">
            <p>The Five Elements (Wu Xing: 五行) are Wood (木), Fire (火), Earth (土), Metal (金), and Water (水). They represent five fundamental energetic phases that cycle through all natural phenomena. Each element governs specific personality traits, body organs, seasons, colors, and directions. They interact through a Production Cycle (each element nourishes the next) and a Control Cycle (each element restrains another). Your personal element balance — visible in your BaZi chart — reveals your strengths, vulnerabilities, and the types of energy you need to cultivate for balance.</p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="about-faq-item">
          <div class="about-faq-q">How do I find my Chinese zodiac animal?</div>
          <div class="about-faq-a">
            <p>Your Chinese zodiac animal is determined by your birth year in the lunar calendar. The 12 animals cycle in fixed order: Rat, Ox, Tiger, Rabbit, Dragon, Snake, Horse, Goat, Monkey, Rooster, Dog, and Pig. However, the Chinese New Year falls between late January and mid-February each year — so if you were born in January or early February, your zodiac animal may actually belong to the previous year. For the most accurate result, use a <a href="/app" style="color:var(--gold,#f0c040);">BaZi calculator</a> that accounts for the exact lunar calendar transition date of your birth year.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- ═══ CTA ═══ -->
    <div class="about-cta">
      <a href="/app" class="btn-primary">Calculate Your BaZi Chart Free →</a>
    </div>

  </main>

  <%- include('../partials/footer') %>

  <script>
    document.querySelectorAll('.about-faq-q').forEach(q => {
      q.addEventListener('click', () => q.closest('.about-faq-item').classList.toggle('open'));
    });
  </script>
</body>
</html>
